# Page Structure Guidelines

## Server Components
- Use server components for data fetching
- Handle authentication and authorization
- Redirect unauthenticated users to login
- Pass data to client components for rendering

## Client Components
- Use client components for interactive elements
- Implement state management with React hooks
- Handle form submissions and user interactions
- Implement client-side validation

## Error Handling
- Implement error boundaries for client components
- Use try/catch blocks for server actions
- Provide user-friendly error messages
- Log errors for debugging

## Loading States
- Implement loading states for data fetching
- Use Suspense for streaming server components
- Show skeleton loaders for content
- Prevent layout shifts during loading

## SEO
- Use metadata for SEO optimization
- Implement proper page titles and descriptions
- Use semantic HTML for better accessibility
- Ensure proper heading hierarchy
